---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import settings from '../content/singletons/settings.json';
---

<Layout
  title="Good Faith Estimate | Morning Light Counseling"
  description="Your right to a Good Faith Estimate of counseling costs under the federal No Surprises Act."
>
  <PageHero title="Your Right to a Good Faith Estimate" />

  <article class="prose-ml mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pb-16 text-lg sm:px-6">
    <p>
      Under the federal <strong>No Surprises Act</strong> (effective January 1, 2022), health care providers are
      required to give clients who don't have insurance — or who choose not to use it — an estimate of the expected
      cost of care, in writing, before services begin.
    </p>

    <h2>What that means here</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Counseling sessions at Morning Light Counseling are <strong>{settings.selfPayRate}</strong> for self-pay
        clients. There are no hidden fees, and you'll never be billed for something we haven't discussed.
      </li>
      <li>
        If you are uninsured or choose to pay out of pocket, you will receive a written Good Faith Estimate of
        expected charges before your first session, and any time you request one.
      </li>
      <li>
        You can ask for a Good Faith Estimate before you schedule anything — just ask when you reach out.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your protections</h2>
    <p>
      If you receive a bill that is at least <strong>$400 more</strong> than your Good Faith Estimate, you have the
      right to dispute it. Make sure to save a copy or a picture of your estimate.
    </p>
    <p>
      For questions or more information about your right to a Good Faith Estimate, visit
      <a href="https://www.cms.gov/nosurprises" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.cms.gov/nosurprises<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
      or call 1-800-985-3059.
    </p>

    <h2>Questions about cost</h2>
    <p>
      Money questions are welcome here — they're a normal part of deciding whether counseling fits your life right
      now. Call {settings.phone} or email {settings.email} and ask anything.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
